<p class="p">Within this perspective, it is necessary to have knowledge of the climate sensitivity 
 <italic class="italic">S</italic>. However, from the perspective of the Paris Agreement, one can define a storyline consisting of a particular global warming level, say 
 <italic class="italic">G</italic> 
 <italic class="italic">=</italic> 
 <italic class="italic">G</italic>
 <sub class="sub">1</sub>, which specifies 
 <italic class="italic">G</italic> deterministically. This condition blocks the influence of 
 <italic class="italic">S</italic>, leaving the truncated factorization 
 <disp-formula id="RSPA20190013M5.5" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">5.5</label>
  <math id="DM5" class="math">
   <mi class="mi">P</mi>
   <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
   <mi class="mi">H</mi>
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">|</mo>
   </mrow>
   <mi class="mi">D</mi>
   <mo class="mo">,</mo>
   <mi class="mi">R</mi>
   <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
   <mi class="mi">P</mi>
   <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
   <mi class="mi">D</mi>
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">|</mo>
   </mrow>
   <mi class="mi">G</mi>
   <mo class="mo">=</mo>
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">G</mi>
     <mn class="mn">1</mn>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
   <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
   <mi class="mi">P</mi>
   <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
   <mi class="mi">R</mi>
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">|</mo>
   </mrow>
   <mi class="mi">G</mi>
   <mo class="mo">=</mo>
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">G</mi>
     <mn class="mn">1</mn>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
   <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
   <mo class="mo">,</mo>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where now the hazard 
 <italic class="italic">H</italic> depends only on the dynamical conditions 
 <italic class="italic">D</italic> and the regional warming 
 <italic class="italic">R</italic>. Note that (5.5) does not imply that 
 <italic class="italic">D</italic> and 
 <italic class="italic">R</italic> are independent; they share a common dependence through 
 <italic class="italic">G</italic>, hence storylines of 
 <italic class="italic">R</italic> may be correlated with storylines of 
 <italic class="italic">D</italic>. This is precisely the basis of the approach of [
 <xref rid="RSPA20190013C16" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">16</xref>].
</p>
